fields.description:
I'm following the instructions here: https://arrow.apache.org/install/

arrow::install_arrow()

gives error:

{{./configure: line 132: cd: libarrow/arrow-0.17.1/lib: No such file or directory}}

{{This leaves me without a working arrow::read_feather.}}

comments.body:
{quote}
I tried installing the binaries with CC and CXX both with gcc 8.3.0 and with the system gcc (4.8.5). I get teh same undefined symbol error (as above) in either case.
{quote}

Odd, I wouldn't expect the _same_ undefined symbol error with those gcc versions. 

{quote}
Error: package or namespace load failed for ‘arrow’ in dyn.load(file, DLLpath = DLLpath, ...):
unable to load shared object '/.../R_4.0.2_libs/00LOCK-arrow/00new/arrow/libs/arrow.so':
/.../R_4.0.2_libs/00LOCK-arrow/00new/arrow/libs/arrow.so: undefined symbol: _ZTIN5boost11regex_errorE
Error: loading failed
{quote}

Could you share the verbose build logs (with {{ARROW_R_DEV=true}} set) from that? And is that using gcc 8 or gcc 4.8? Boost regex is only needed when compiling with gcc < 4.9.

I am not sure if I should be mentioning it here, but I am getting the same "undefined symbol: _ZN6snappy11RawCompressEPKcmPcPm" error on CentOS 7, and I found that I could install an old version of arrow with
{code:java}
PackageUrl <- "https://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/Archive/arrow/arrow_0.16.0.2.tar.gz" install.packages(PackageUrl, repos=NULL, type="source") {code}
So the issue may have been introduced into the build process between 0.16.0.2 and 0.17.1 (I haven't tried 0.17.0 yet).
